{"id": 20491, "date": "1988-08-10T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1988-08-10T18:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=20491"}, "modified": "2026-02-23T17:58:37", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-24T01:58:37", "slug": "matr-dion-bruce-springsteen-paul-simon-lou-reed-james-taylor-billy-joel-and-reuben-blades-a-teenager-in-love", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/08/10/matr-dion-bruce-springsteen-paul-simon-lou-reed-james-taylor-billy-joel-and-reuben-blades-a-teenager-in-love/", "title": {"rendered": "A Teenager in Love"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>They weren&#8217;t the Belmonts, but they&#8217;d do in a pinch.</p>\n<p>On the evening of December 13, 1987, Paul Simon organized a benefit concert at Madison Square Garden in order to raise awareness and money to fight homelessness among New York City&#8217;s children.</p>\n<p>The announced line-up was stellar on its own: Simon, of course, along with his Graceland tour mates Ladysmith Black Mambazo; James Taylor, Chaka Khan, Reuben Blades, Dion DiMucci, and Lou Reed were on the bill, too.</p>\n<p>But it was the unadvertised guests during Dion&#8217;s set that sent the crowd through the roof: along with Paul Simon, Lou Reed, James Taylor, and Reuben Blades, Dion surprised the crowd by inviting Billy Joel and Bruce Springsteen to be his honorary Belmonts for the evening.</p>\n<p>Together, the all-star ensemble performed Dion&#8217;s 1959 classic, &#8220;A Teenager in Love.&#8221; (Watch to the end to see Bruce get in one last doo-wop hook.)</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9hJOwe0vH_s?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;A Teenager in Love&#8221; peaked at #5 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1959. It was one of Dion&#8217;s greatest hits and is almost universally known and loved to this day.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2pwgswchPDo?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>A Teenager in Love<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> September 30, 1976 (West Hollywood, CA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> December 13, 1987 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 August 16, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce Springsteen, Billy Joel, James Taylor, Lou Reed, Reuben Blades, and Paul Simon serve as honorary Belmonts for Dion&#8217;s 1987 benefit performance of &#8220;A Teenager in Love.&#8221;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 67952, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "